.TH PIZZAFOOL 6 "1 March 2026" "CDE/Motif"
.IX "pizzafool" "" "\fLpizzafool\fP \(em Mr. T's graphical pizza menu user interface"
.SH NAME
pizzafool \- I pity the fool who don't use this pizza program!
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pizzafool
.SH DESCRIPTION
Listen up, sucka!
.I PizzaFool
is THE pizza ordering program, and Mr. T is your host.
Some fool at Sun made a program called
.IR PizzaTool (6)
back in the day for that NeWS window system, but Mr. T don't mess with
no NeWS \(em Mr. T uses Motif like a REAL man!
You pick your toppings, you see your pizza, and Mr. T tells you
what he thinks about your choices. And Mr. T ALWAYS tells you
what he thinks, fool!
.PP
On the left side you got TWELVE topping checkboxes.
Mr. T approves of Pepperoni, Mushrooms, Sausage, Extra Cheese, and Onions \(em
those are toppings for people who ain't fools.
Green Peppers, Black Olives, Jalape\361os, and BBQ Chicken are
QUESTIONABLE \(em Mr. T's got his eye on you, sucka.
And if you even THINK about clicking Pineapple, Anchovies, or
Artichoke Hearts, I PITY YOU, FOOL!
That ain't pizza, that's a CRIME!
.PP
Below the toppings you pick your size. You got four choices:
Small is the Fool-size \(em that's for fools who don't know how to eat.
Medium is the Sucka-size.
Large is the Mr. T size, and that's the DEFAULT, because Mr. T
don't eat no small pizza!
Family is the A-Team size \(em that's when the whole team is hungry, sucka!
.PP
On the right side of the window, you see ME \(em Mr. T \(em
in one of TWELVE different poses, rendered in 256 glorious colors.
When you pick good toppings, Mr. T looks happy.
When you pick questionable toppings, Mr. T gives you the LOOK.
And when you pick something TERRIBLE like pineapple?
Mr. T goes OFF, fool! You been warned!
.PP
Below my picture there's a text area where Mr. T delivers his
wisdom about your pizza choices IN REAL TIME.
You better read it, sucka!
.PP
At the bottom you got three buttons, and you better know which ones to press:
.TP
.B "Order Pizza, Fool!"
This is the button for people who ain't cowards!
Press it and Mr. T orders your pizza. Mr. T will tell you exactly
what you ordered, and remind you to TIP THE DELIVERY DRIVER, fool!
But if you press this with NO toppings selected, Mr. T is gonna
let you KNOW what he thinks about that!
.TP
.B "Show Pizza, Fool!"
Press this and a ROUND WINDOW pops up showing a picture of your pizza
with all the toppings you picked! You change the toppings, the pizza
changes too \(em it's LIVE, sucka! Mr. T don't show you no stale pizza!
You can resize the window to get a closer look, because Mr. T
believes in ATTENTION TO DETAIL!
.TP
.B "Quit (Coward!)"
This button is for QUITTERS. Mr. T is disappointed in you if you
press this, but Mr. T respects your freedom to be a coward. Go on, fool.
.PP
The pizza preview paints a real nice pizza with crust, sauce, cheese,
and all your toppings spread out using some MATHEMATICS that Mr. T
don't need to explain to you \(em just know it looks GOOD.
The drawing code came from the original
.I PizzaTool
program, but Mr. T ported it from that fancy PostScript stuff to
X11 drawing calls, because Mr. T don't need no stinkin' PostScript!
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PIZZAFOOL_IMAGES
This tells Mr. T where to find his twelve pictures, fool!
If you don't set it, Mr. T looks in
.BR ./images ,
which is where a SMART person puts 'em.
.TP
.B DISPLAY
The X display. You better HAVE one, fool!
Mr. T needs an 8-bit PseudoColor visual with 256 colors,
like what's on a real Sun framebuffer. Mr. T don't mess with
no 24-bit TrueColor \(em 256 colors was good enough for the A-Team
and it's good enough for YOU, sucka!
.SH FILES
.TP
.B images/mrt_*.xpm
Twelve pictures of Mr. T in XPM format. Every single one uses
a shared 200-color palette with Floyd-Steinberg dithering, because
Mr. T don't WASTE no colormap entries, fool!
Mr. T is efficient. Be like Mr. T.
.SH NOTES
Mr. T built this program for Solaris 7 with CDE on his
SPARCstation 4, and it runs on that sun4m hardware like a
CHAMP. It loads XPM files WITHOUT libXpm \(em Mr. T wrote
his OWN loader, because Mr. T don't depend on nobody!
And when the colormap gets full (because CDE takes up
about 56 colors like some kind of FOOL), Mr. T's program
finds the NEAREST color instead of giving up. Mr. T
NEVER gives up!
.PP
Mr. T rates every topping from 0 to 2 on the
.I terribleness
scale. Zero means Mr. T approves. One means Mr. T has
his DOUBTS about you. Two means Mr. T PITIES you, fool!
Pineapple, anchovies, and artichoke hearts are ALL twos.
You been warned, sucka!
.PP
.I PizzaTool
was made by some smart people at Sun for that NeWS window system.
Mr. T RESPECTS those people \(em they had vision.
.I PizzaFool
is Mr. T's tribute to their work, rewritten from SCRATCH for
Motif, because Mr. T builds things RIGHT!
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR pizzatool (6),
.IR X (1),
.IR mwm (1),
.IR dtlogin (1)
.SH BUGS
There ain't no way to pay your tab. Mr. T says you better
figure that out yourself, fool!
.PP
Mr. T cannot actually deliver pizza through your screen.
Mr. T WISHES he could, but even Mr. T has limits. VERY FEW limits.
.PP
The pizza don't spin like it did in the original
.IR PizzaTool .
Mr. T don't need no spinning pizza \(em the pizza RESPECTS Mr. T
enough to stay STILL!
